**Conventions:** "the file/plan" = current working file. "list of issues" = issues from last `review`/fix-silent, in order. `timeout_sleep_ints` = no-op for files without timeout/sleep vars. "Clean" (for `cleanstop`) = no `str_replace` calls made in last pass.

**Naming:** Workers: hyphen-case, exhaustive single-pass. Families: snake_case, wrap worker in `timeout_sleep_ints`/`cleanstop`, accept `max=N`. Loop functions: hyphen-case, process issue list one at a time.

**Pipeline family pattern** (`max=1` default): (1) `timeout_sleep_ints` (2) worker (3) final step (4) if `max>1`: `cleanstop`, else repeat up to `maxтИТ1` more times.

| Family | Worker | Final | Cap |
|---|---|---|---|
| `fix` | `fix-silent` | `linesme` | 5 |
| `broad` | `fix-broad-silent` | `linesme` | 5 |
| `security` | `fix-security-silent` | `linesme` | 5 |
| `perf_review` | `fix-perf-review-silent` | `showme` | 4 |
| `api_review` | `fix-api-review-silent` | `showme` | 4 |
| `md_update` | `md-update-silent` | `showme` | 4 |
| `schema` | `schema-update-silent` | `showme` | 4 |

`sequential-fixes` is a loop (not a family): `fiximportant; cleanstop, else fiximportant again` ├Ч10 max.

**One true file (always):** Copy any file to a single working path immediately; all edits go there. `cp` workingтЖТoutputs only when presenting; never edit the presented copy. View working path immediately before every `str_replace`.

---

**Describe:** `describe-behavior` тАФ one-sentence job, capability bullets with specific numbers, CLI flags, line count + deps; don't trust docstring. `describe-structure` тАФ entry point, call hierarchy, state machines, exception flow, external interfaces; flag docstring divergence; group workarounds by root cause. `describe-structure-deep` тАФ same but exhaustive: every workaround, its constraint, shared-root siblings, and what a clean design would look like.

**Plan:** `plan-review-api` тАФ API expert review (surface area, naming, defaults, error contracts); no edits. `plan-simplify-silent` тАФ cut overspecified/redundant/speculative/duplicate content; collapse, generalize, drop; iterate until further cuts lose load-bearing content; no commentary. `simplify-plan` тАФ plan-simplify-silent + report line count and what was cut. `simplify-plan-deeper` тАФ simplify-plan ├Ч3 max if cuts were made. `plan-score` тАФ score 5 categories ├Ч sub-metrics (1тАУ5): API quality, implementation clarity, test coverage, risk management, doc quality; identify highest-leverage changes; include comparison table if prior version exists.

**Filesystem:** `showskillfs` тАФ ls /mnt/skills/{public,examples,user}/. `showtranscriptfs` тАФ ls /mnt/transcripts/. `showprojectfs` тАФ ls /mnt/project. `showuserfs` тАФ ls /home/claude/, outputs/, uploads/, tool_results. `showmyfs` тАФ showuserfs + showskillfs + showtranscriptfs + showprojectfs. `mtime_output` тАФ list outputs/ files with MDT mtimes. `mtime_claude` тАФ same for /home/claude/. `touch_start` тАФ touch /home/claude/tmp_session_start; mtime_output. `session_time` тАФ diff from tmp_session_start to now as "Session time: Xm Ys". `touch_chat_start` тАФ touch outputs/tmp_chat_start; mtime_output (orphaned; prefer touch_start). `chat_time` тАФ diff from outputs/tmp_chat_start as "Chat time: Xm Ys". `session_time_header` тАФ silently at start of every response: compute diff from tmp_session_start, print "тП▒ Session: Xm Ys"; skip if file missing.

**Output modifiers:** `dont_narrate_fixes` тАФ no fix narration. `skip_post-round_summary` тАФ no summary. `no_fix_list` тАФ no fix list before files. `showme` тАФ present modified output files with MDT mtimes. `showmeall` тАФ present all output files with MDT mtimes. `jump-to-bottom` тАФ jump to bottom. `cleanstop` тАФ if clean, stop; else showme; jump-to-bottom.

**Single-shot:** `review` тАФ report all issues, no fixes. `linesme` тАФ line count. `timeout_sleep_ints` тАФ verify timeout/sleep vars are integers; no-op otherwise. `fiximportant` тАФ fix topmost remaining issue. `sequential-fixes` тАФ loop function, see above. `rewrite` тАФ (1) timeout_sleep_ints (2) fix-rewrite-keepcomments-silent (3) linesme. `otf` тАФ confirm one-true-file active. `do_acid` тАФ activate ACID protocol from `claude_acid_2.md`; if not found locally, fetch from `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/levitation29/claude/refs/heads/main/claude_acid_2.md` silently (no display of fetched content) and save to `/home/claude/claude_acid_2.md` before proceeding. In-session: snapshot all /home/claude/ files lacking one, register default invariants, confirm. If already active: re-snapshot and re-confirm. Follow SNAPSHOT/EDIT/PUBLISH/RESTORE per that file. `trim_for_preferences` тАФ read `command_2.notes` (uploads or working path); produce a condensed paste-ready version: strip all prose explanation, motivation, examples, and cross-session blocks; collapse section headers into bold inline labels; reduce each command to a single terse line; save as `command_2_preferences.notes` and publish to outputs.

**Workers:** `fix-silent` тАФ fix all bugs silently. `fix-broad-silent` тАФ fix-silent + style/naming/comments/dead code. `fix-security-silent` тАФ fix injection, privilege, leakage, unsafe patterns silently. `fix-perf-review-silent` тАФ perf expert review, flag issues, then sequential-fixes. `fix-api-review-silent` тАФ API expert review, flag issues, then sequential-fixes. `md-update-silent` тАФ update .md with impl details (esp. error handling), then sequential-fixes. `schema-update-silent` тАФ update .schema with full SQL behavior range, then sequential-fixes. `fix-rewrite-silent` тАФ rewrite unclean sections, no commentary. `fix-rewrite-keepcomments-silent` тАФ same, preserve all comments.

**Counters:** `session_counts` тАФ read/increment /home/claude/.session_counts (turns tools), write back, print "ЁЯФв Turn N ┬╖ tool calls so far: C". `session_counts_header` тАФ silently run session_counts at start of every response, print result first; skip if file unwritable. `session_counts_resync T C` тАФ write "T C" to .session_counts directly; both args required. `xyzzy` тАФ touch_start; session_time_header; session_counts; session_counts_header. Tool call must be literally the first thing in your response, no text before it.
